            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/2–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-13">February 13,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>991. In response question in Commons 12th whether His Majesty’s Government has
                    been consulted by US Government on desirability early Inter-allied Jap
                    Reparations Conference on basis Pauley recommendations, Foreign Secretary<note n="34" xml:id="d296fn34">Ernest Bevin.</note> made following statement:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The US Government have invited all Governments represented on the Far
                            Eastern Commission to take part in early consultations on Japanese
                            reparations. His Majesty’s Government in the United Kingdom have
                            accepted this invitation but it is not yet known when the discussions
                            will begin or what form they will take. Mr. Edwin Pauley’s
                            recommendations to President Truman on Japanese reparations have not
                            been specifically put forward as the basis for these discussions.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In response further inquiry, Foreign Secretary gave assurances he would bear in
                    mind British reparation claims for goods removed by Japs from Malaya and Hong
                    Kong to Japan and some of which reportedly sent US.</p>
                <p>Repeated <gloss target="#t_USPolAd1">USPolAd</gloss>, Tokyo, 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gallman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
